    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This issue can be fixed easily by only adding:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    if (query === '') {\r\n        helper.search(); // <-- still do a search when query is empty, fixes the urlSync on first letter\r\n\t    return;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nSo in the end, the usecase being \"hide hits when no query\" and not \"do not do any search when query is empty\", we could mark this as fixed and answer the person..\r\n\r\n\r\nWDYT?",
